For secuirty 

For Enable automatic security updates
sudo apt install unattended-upgrades apt-listchanges -y
sudo dpkg-reconfigure unattended-upgrades

Verify:
cat /etc/apt/apt.conf.d/50unattended-upgrades

Enable firewall

sudo apt install ufw -y
sudo ufw default deny incoming
sudo ufw default allow outgoing

Allow required services only

sudo ufw allow OpenSSH
sudo ufw allow 80
sudo ufw allow 443
sudo ufw enable

sudo ufw status verbose


update below on this path: sudo nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config

AllowTcpForwarding no
MaxAuthTries 3

sudo systemctl restart ssh

Fail2Ban (Stops Brute Force Attacks)

sudo apt install fail2ban -y

Create config:

sudo cp /etc/fail2ban/jail.conf /etc/fail2ban/jail.local

update in this file below settings: sudo nano /etc/fail2ban/jail.local

[sshd]
enabled = true
port = ssh
maxretry = 3
bantime = 1h

sudo systemctl restart fail2ban
fail2ban-client status sshd

